Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%mins}. Break up the
mince as it cooks.

  > IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
  > no pink in the middle.

Put the @couscous{120%grams} into a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @boiling water{200%milliliters} and stir in half the
@chicken stock paste{20%grams}.

Cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side, ~{10%mins}.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic to the beef and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Stir in the sweetcorn, @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%grams}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder), @honey{1%tbsp},
@butter{20%grams} and the remaining chicken stock paste.

Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{2-3%mins}.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{}. Share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the chipotle beef.

Add a dollop of @soured cream{75%grams}.

Enjoy!